<div class="wp-block-column" style="flex-basis:60%"><!-- wp:paragraph {"textColor":"contrast","style":{"typography":{"fontSize":"1rem","lineHeight":"1.75","fontFamily":"var:preset|font-family|body","fontWeight":"200"}}} -->
<p class="has-contrast-color has-text-color" style="font-family:var(--wp--preset--font-family--body);font-size:1rem;font-weight:200;line-height:1.75">Originally built in 1887 as a merchant's warehouse in South Mumbai, The Colaba Vault lay dormant for decades before Concrete &amp; Light was commissioned to transform it into a world-class contemporary art gallery.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"textColor":"contrast","style":{"typography":{"fontSize":"1rem","lineHeight":"1.75","fontFamily":"var:preset|font-family|body","fontWeight":"200"},"spacing":{"margin":{"top":"1.25rem"}}}} -->
<p class="has-contrast-color has-text-color" style="margin-top:1.25rem;font-family:var(--wp--preset--font-family--body);font-size:1rem;font-weight:200;line-height:1.75">New board-formed concrete walls were threaded through the original stone arches, creating a sequence of intimate gallery rooms within the expansive warehouse shell. Zenithal skylights replace the deteriorated roof structure, flooding each space with the diffused tropical light that Mumbai offers so generously.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"textColor":"contrast","style":{"typography":{"fontSize":"1rem","lineHeight":"1.75","fontFamily":"var:preset|font-family|body","fontWeight":"200"},"spacing":{"margin":{"top":"1.25rem"}}}} -->
<p class="has-contrast-color has-text-color" style="margin-top:1.25rem;font-family:var(--wp--preset--font-family--body);font-size:1rem;font-weight:200;line-height:1.75">The project received the UNESCO Asia-Pacific Award for Cultural Heritage Conservation in 2024, recognising the sensitive balance between preservation and contemporary architectural expression.</p>
